":"1480","about 1450":"about 1450","about 1472":"about 1472","1449":"1449","of Dalegarth, Cumberland, England":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","Dalegarth, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom","Hooton, Cheshire, England":"Hooton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Dalegarth, Cumberland, England":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Stanley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Stanley, including those in Yorkshire, Staffordshire, Derbyshire, Durham, Gloucestershire, and Wiltshire, named with Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. This English name has been established in Ireland since the 13th century where it was Gaelicized as <b>de Stainléigh</b>.","English: possibly also a variant of <b>Stoneley</b>, a habitational name from Stoneley Green in Burland (Cheshire), Stoneleigh (Warwickshire), or Stonely in Kimbolton (Huntingdonshire), all named with Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Americanized form of any of various like-sounding names in other languages, for example Polish   Stanislawski  , Greek   Anastasiou  , and Serbian <b>Stojadinov</b> (patronymic from the personal name <i>Stojadin</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Stanislawski","meanings":["Polish (<b>Stanisławski</b>): habitational name for someone from any of various places called Stanisław, Stanisławów, or Stanisławice, named with the personal name <i>Stanisław</i> (see   Stanislav  )."]},{"name":"Standley","meanings":["English: variant of   Stanley  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Stanley was born about 1450, in Dalegarth, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Stanley, was 28 and his mother, Ann Hudleston, was 27. He married Alice Duckett about 1472, in Dalegarth, Cumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 3 March 1512, in Hooton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 63."},"et":{"about 1450–3 Mar 1512":"umbes 1450–3. märts 1512","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1451–Female":"1451–Surnud","1480–1556":"1480–1556","1424–Male":"1424–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1556":"1556","1512":"1512","1451":"1451","1450":"1450","3 Mar 1512":"3. märts 1512","1480":"1480","about 1450":"umbes 1450","about 1472":"umbes 1472","1449":"1449","of Dalegarth, Cumberland, England":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dalegarth, Cumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hooton, Cheshire, England":"Hooton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dalegarth, Cumberland, England":"Dalegarth, Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"about 1450–3 Mar 1512":"noin 1450–3. maaliskuuta 1512","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1451–Female":"1451–Kuollut","1480–1556":"1480–1556","1424–Male":"1424–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","1425":"1425","1424":"1424","1556":"1556","1512":"1512","1451":"1451","1450":"1450","3 Mar 1512":"3. maaliskuuta 1512","1480":"1480","about 1450":"noin 1450"